    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm currently using the following autocmd in my `init.lua`. It's purpose is to organize organize the imports which requires modifying the buffer. But when it is triggered by `BufWritePre` the buffer gets saved to the file before `vim.lsp.buf.code_action` applies the changes.\r\n\r\nThe result is that the changes are made in the buffer but not included in the saved file.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"BufWritePre\" }, {\r\n    pattern = \"*.go\",\r\n    command = \"lua vim.lsp.buf.code_action({ context = { only = { 'source.organizeImports' } }, apply = true })\"\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe [LSP FAQ](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html) addresses a similar use-case using `vim.lsp.buf.format()` and its `async` option as an example.\r\n\r\nI imagine the same async option could be added to `vim.lsp.buf.code_action`.\r\n\r\nI don't know any lua and after looking at the code for 5 minutes it seems non-trivial for me to attempt to fix this. I'm therefore making this feature request here.",
